author: Suhas Nayse
title: All India volleyball tourney in Nagpur from Oct 15
text:
NAGPUR: Vidya Bharti, Nagpur is holding the 28th all India volleyball championship for U-14 boys and girls on October 15 and 16 here at the Venus Sports Association ground, Reshimbag.
Vidya Bharti Vidarbha sanghatan mantri Shrikant Deshpande said eight boys and seven girls teams from various parts of the country will participate in the two-day tourney. Last year, Nagpur girls, representing West Zone, had emerged winners at Gwalior. The winning team will automatically qualifies for the SGFI Nationals.
The matches will be played on league cum knockout basis. Maharashtra energy minister Chandrashekhar Bawankule and vice-president of Volleyball Federation of India Vijay Dangre will inaugurate the tournament at 8 am on Thursday.
The prize distribution function will be held on October 16. Mayor Pravin Datke will be the chief guest on the occasion.
